5000|$|Safe {{semantics}} is a consistency {{model that}} describes one <b>type</b> <b>of</b> <b>guarantee</b> a data register provides {{when it is}} shared by several processors in a parallel machine or in a network of computers working together.This notion was first defined by Lamport in 1985. Later on, it was formally defined in Leslie Lamport's [...] "On Interprocess Communication", {{which was published in}} Distributed Computing in 1986.|$|E
