40|$|Abstract—In this work, {{we present}} how {{programmable}} data-plane technology (software routers) offers an easy-to-apply mech-anism to create virtual wireless networks and support buffering and scheduling decisions. Furthermore, {{we present a}} feedback-based buffering mechanism that is able to provide throughput ratio guarantees per virtual network, without requiring any mod-ifications in the 802. 11 driver and without relying on statistical knowledge of the workload per virtual network or knowledge regarding the channel conditions. We implement the proposed mechanism in a software router in a 802. 11 Access Point and we evaluate its performance in a wireless testbed environment. The methodology and the mechanics developed are generic and with some modifications {{can be applied to}} differentiating services for other <b>types</b> <b>of</b> <b>guarantees</b> like delay...|$|R
